Thinking about hiring another Josh?

Hiring a developer doesnt need to be intimidating or complicated.

Read more below to learn everything you need to know to about Joshua Green, from dancing to development.

Development, The Way It Should Be

Youll be surprised with how quickly I can burn through tasks, with the speed of the landing pages I build, and how fast I can get through a sentence. One surprise you dont want is to be caught off guard by inadequate development when you need it the most.

You Might Get a Kick Out of This

In middle school I started ballroom dancing and after a couple years I started dancing at the Vibe studio. Although I later gave up dancing for debate, several members from that ballroom team are currently dancing professionally for Dancing With the Stars.

There are a lot of reasons why Josh would do well at Homie

  1. Blazing fast load times

    Using a fast website is easy, making one is not. Page speed and asset optimization are essential to any web project and scoring well with any page speed tool takes proper image optimization, caching tools, and a clean code base.

  2. Passionate about design

    "Good Enough" won't cut it, always build something you can be proud of. From building email templates to landing pages, consistent attention to detail is essential to maintainint brand integrity.

  3. Quality Code, On Time

    Either you have the time to build it right, or you'll make the time to build it twice. Its absolutely necessary to understand the how fundamental elements work together, and to plan how each piece will be used to create your final product,

  4. Always Learning

    The industry is always growing and changing, you have to work to keep up. Learning is an essential part of this industry, and by far the best way to keep yourself from becoming bored with work. There is always more to learn, and a better way to build your next project.

  5. Fun at Parties

    Did you know that Male Platypuses have poison glands in their thighs that inject via a hollow spur near the heel? Did you know that Black Holes aren't really black? Actually I don't really know about that, but the platypus thing is true!
